{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"08acecae-7f27-4d57-a495-172074f836cb","content":"For **tests**, use `dotnet watch test` — not `dotnet test` or `dotnet run`. The `dotnet watch` command is what triggers hot reload; it monitors for file changes and re-runs automatically.\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nNeither `dotnet test` nor `dotnet run` on their own support hot reload — they execute once and exit. The `watch` verb is the key.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"78838ef7-6494-43d4-b4aa-f44da838d705","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at the project files to understand the context better.","outputTokens":145},"id":"0a76257c-2fde-4f8b-aea4-01a9aca6cc59","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:17.496Z","parentId":"a1ef9a8d-4f9d-4896-9029-91b1ee53f86a"}
